OL,3,CWho controls my local council in
OL,4,CLondon?
OL,6,FCouncillors are elected every four
OL,7,Fyears. The party (or independent
OL,8,Fgroup) with the most councillors
OL,9,Fusually takes control and appoints a
OL,10,Fcouncil leader.
OL,12,FThen there's the City of London - the
OL,13,Fhistoric Square Mile - which is
OL,14,Fgoverned separately by the City of
OL,15,FLondon Corporation which traces its
OL,16,Froots back to medieval times. It works
OL,17,Flike a council, but businesses as well
OL,18,Fas residents get votes in local
OL,19,Felections.
